reviewText: Love Dr. G. She explains so much about the things that can go wrong in the body. We hear about high blood pressure, diabetes, obesity, drug abuse, etc. so much that I think we forget just how serious these diseases can be. Dr. G. lets us know in detail the sequence of events that take place to cause death in the cases she handles.

reviewText: I am a postmortem  buff and by that I mean I like to watch dead people being medically examined to ascertain the actual cause of death. In our  modern society, a dead body being discovered would be suspected of foul play and would initially be classified as homicide until it is thoroughly examined by a qualified pathologist in a hospital morgue. I will look forward with keen expectation and interest to receive this dvd and watch the full lenght feature film. I hope that this one dvd contains 12 episodes as advertised by Amazon.com rather than six when I receive as one reviewer complained recently...!  In the past, I have bought and watched The Autopsy Files which featured the renowned forensic pathologist, Dr. Michael Baden, and also Autopsy: A post mortem review by Dr. Michael Baden himself.  Additionally, I have also read the book on the same subject by Dr. Baden. I hope Amazon. com would introduce more dvds on autopsy because this subject is both educational and informative for the general public which has otherwise no  access to such scientific information on death and the scientific study of cadavers....! Thanks.

reviewText: We haven't really watched any other autopsy shows.  This one is interesting, as some cases are tragic and others bizarre.  I think Dr. G is fairly preachy, often commenting on how you should check your blood pressure, etc. so you don't end up dead for the same reason these people did.
